  <h2>Automatic Detection</h2>
  <p>
    RefleK's is designed to work out of the box. When you first launch it, it
    will automatically:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Detect your KovaaK's stats folder from your Steam installation</li>
    <li>Start monitoring for new scenario runs</li>
    <li>Import your existing stats history</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Default Settings</h2>
  <p>RefleK's comes with sensible defaults that work for most users:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Stats folder:</strong> Automatically detected from your KovaaK's installation
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Session gap:</strong> 20 minutes (runs within this gap are grouped together)
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Mouse tracking:</strong> Disabled by default (enable in settings if
      desired)
    </li>
    <li><strong>Theme:</strong> Dark mode</li>
    <li><strong>Autostart:</strong> Disabled by default</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Autostart with KovaaK's</h2>
  <p>RefleK's can start automatically when you launch KovaaK's:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Open Settings (gear icon in the top right)</li>
    <li>Go to General → Autostart with KovaaK's</li>
    <li>Toggle it on</li>
  </ol>
  <p>
    When enabled, RefleK's starts hidden with Windows and opens automatically
    when KovaaK's launches. Closing the window keeps it running in memory for
    quick access.
  </p>

  <h2>Manual Configuration</h2>
  <p>
    If RefleK's can't detect your stats folder automatically, you can set it
    manually:
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>Open Settings (gear icon in the top right)</li>
    <li>Go to General → Stats Folder</li>
    <li>Enter the path to your KovaaK's stats folder</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="image-container">
    <img
      src="/assets/images/settings.webp"
      alt="RefleK's settings panel"
      loading="lazy"
    />
  </div>

  <p>The default stats folder location is:</p>
  <p>
    <code
      >C:\Program Files
      (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\FPSAimTrainer\FPSAimTrainer\stats</code
    >
  </p>

  <div class="note">
    <strong>Tip:</strong> If you have a custom Steam library location, the stats folder
    will be in that library's steamapps folder.
  </div>

  <h2>Steam Integration</h2>
  <p>
    For benchmark rankings, RefleK's detects your Steam username from your local
    Steam installation and uses it to fetch your progress from KovaaK's servers.
    This is automatic on Windows - no Steam profile visibility settings
    required.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
